  "text": "Nucleic Acids Research, 2015, Vol. 43, No. 10 e67 ses revealed that 18 of the 265 genes enriched the electron transport. This function was confirmed by a previous study where genes related to it were differentially regulated under the ethanol stress condition, to overcome energy shortage caused by inhibition of glycolysis [CITATION_1] . The other most enriched pathways/functional categories include glutamate synthase and cell envelop. Our detailed enrichment data are given in Supplementary file 2. Further investigation of these differentially arranged TUs could potentially reveal more insights into gene function and regulation relevant to ethanol stress and responses.",
